hints_latex:
The stationary probability density, $\bar{\mathbf{p}}$, satisfies the
equation:

\begin{align*}
\bar{\mathbf{p}} = P\bar{\mathbf{p}}.
\end{align*}

statement_latex:
Consider a random walk that has transition matrix:

\begin{align*}
P=\begin{bmatrix}
1/4  &  1/4  &  1/4\\
3/4  &  3/4  &  1/4\\
0  &  0  &  1/2
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

Find the equilibrium probability vector (i.e. the vector at which
probabilities remain unchanged from one step to the next).
